<TITLE> Truck driver dies in road accident </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajbari, May 3 (bdnews24.com) A truck driver died and his helper was injured in a road accident at Rajbari on Sunday midnight. The dead is Siraj Ahmed, 30, son of Abdul Mannan of Benapole in Jessore. His assistant, Ebrahim, 22, was seriously injured and admitted to Faridpur Medical College Hospital. The police said that the truck began to malfunction near Basantapur Railway Station on the Daulatdia-Khulna highway in Rajbari. The driver and his helper then got down and were trying to repair the truck when a Khulna-bound bus of Hanif Paribahan, a private bus company, hit the truck from behind. The police said that Siraj died on the spot. His body was sent to Rajbari Sadr Hospital for post mortem. The police had seized the bus but its driver managed to flee. A case was filed with the Rajbari Sadr Police Station. bd
